value.title: Biden, top Democrats lay groundwork for multibillion dollar push to boost U.S. broadband
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden and top congressional Democrats are laying the groundwork to seek a massive increase in federal broadband spending next year, hoping they can secure billions of dollars in new government aid to improve internet access and affordability -- and help people stay online during the pandemic.

value.title: Trump reportedly told an ally he knows he lost the 2020 election but wants revenge on Democrats for disputing his 2016 win
value.excerpt: He is refusing to concede partly because he is still furious that Barack Obama and Hillary Clinton said Russia helped him win in 2016, CNN reported.

value.title: New York subpoenas Trump Organization records on consulting fees paid to Ivanka
value.excerpt: New York’s attorney general has sent a subpoena to the Trump Organization for records related to consulting fees paid to Ivanka Trump.

value.title: Romney rips Trump in late-night tweet, calls president's actions effort to ‘subvert’ will of people
value.excerpt: Sen. Mitt Romney, R-Utah, took to Twitter late Thursday to rip President Trump, saying the president had failed to make “even a plausible case of widespread fraud or conspiracy before a court of law” pertaining to the 2020 presidential election.

value.title: Trump administration does not support lockdown, school closures: Pence
value.excerpt: The Trump administration does not support another lockdown or school closures to stem the spread of the deadly coronavirus, Vice President Mike Pence said on Thursday, even as infections have hit record highs in recent days in the United States.

value.title: Mitt Romney calls Trump's attempt to overturn Michigan election 'undemocratic'
value.excerpt: Two prominent Republican senators on Thursday ripped President Donald Trump's attempt to overturn the results of the presidential election in Michigan, with one going so far as to call the President's strategy "undemocratic."

value.title: Harvard petition demands ‘accountability’ before Trump officials are invited to campus
value.excerpt: Trump allies, including Kayleigh McEnany and Alan Dershowitz, decried the open letter from Harvard affiliates and vowed to challenge it.

value.title: Promising more lawsuits, Trump attorney Rudy Giuliani recycles litany of debunked claims
value.excerpt: Rudy Giuliani on Thursday staged a bizarre 90-minute press conference where they outlined plans to resurrect a crumbling legal strategy.

value.title: Biden says Federal Reserve's interest rate policy has been 'positive'
value.excerpt: U.S. President-elect Joe Biden on Thursday said he supports the way the Federal Reserve has managed interest rate policy and that he has selected a person to run the Treasury Department.

value.title: NJ Dem congressman has called for Trump to be tried for 'crimes against the United States'
value.excerpt: Staunch critic of President Trump, Rep. Bill Pascrell Jr., D-N.J., has called for Trump and members of his administration to be investigated and prosecuted once he leaves office.

value.title: New 'squad' member suggests Biden needs to pay minority communities back after election support
value.excerpt: Congressman-elect Jamaal Bowman, D-N.Y., indicated on Thursday that President-elect Joe Biden owed Black and Brown people after they helped elect him.

value.title: Biden paints Trump as reckless as Pence and science advisers cheer vaccine news
value.excerpt: At dueling public events, the president-elect and the White House offered starkly different views of Trump’s pandemic response.

value.title: Pence on virus: US 'has never been more prepared'
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence offered an upbeat assessment of the coronavirus situation in the U.S., despite a surge in cases, hospitalizations and more than 250,000 deaths. He spoke at the first coronavirus task force briefing in months.

value.title: Trump's refusal to concede creates strange gap between Biden and Harris on classified intelligence
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris took part in a classified briefing of the Senate Intelligence Committee this week and emerged in a strange position -- being more informed about current threats than President-elect Joe Biden but bound by congressional rules to keep that information from him.

value.title: Pence to campaign Friday in Georgia runoffs, but no word on a Trump trip
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence heads to Georgia on Friday, to campaign with Sens. David Perdue and Kelly Loeffler, the Republican incumbents in the state’s twin Senate runoff elections. But there's no word on whether President Trump will head to Georgia.

value.title: The Latest: Pence offers positive COVID-19 assessment in US
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence is offering an upbeat assessment of the status of the coronavirus in the U.S., despite a surge in cases, hospitalizations and more than a quarter of a million deaths. Pence says President Donald Trump directed that Thursday’s briefing be held.

value.title: Trump faces economic redline
value.excerpt: When it comes to who’s-telling-whom, economic interests usually dictate political actions.

value.title: Washington Post: Trump spoke to GOP official who now wants to 'rescind' vote to certify Detroit's results
value.excerpt: The two Republican members of the Wayne County Board of Canvassers want to "rescind" their votes to certify the presidential results from the county, the largest in Michigan and home to the city of Detroit, even though the board has already certified the results.

value.title: Trump campaign drops lawsuit challenging Michigan voting results
value.excerpt: President Trump's reelection campaign said Thursday that it is dropping a lawsuit challenging voting results in Michigan, which show Democrat Joe Biden narrowly carrying the battleground state.

value.title: Biden hasn't said anything on Newsom dinner controversy amid COVID-19 spike
value.excerpt: California Gov. Gavin Newsom is still facing backlash for dining at a restaurant with a large group while pushing new coronavirus restrictions on indoor dining during a spike in cases, and President-elect Joe Biden has yet to weigh in on the matter.

value.title: Biden tells governors he’ll help states overcome coronavirus
value.excerpt: In a virtual meeting with governors, Joe Biden has expressed concern that President Donald Trump’s unprecedented attempt to block the peaceful transition of power at the White House has hindered the f

value.title: Former GSA administrator: 'It's clear' we should recognize Biden as the President-elect
value.excerpt: The former head of the General Services Administration during the 2000 election said Thursday that he would ascertain the 2020 results and begin the formal transition to a Joe Biden presidency, which the current administrator has yet to do.

value.title: Fact check: Map showing Trump landslide based on false report of seized election servers in Germany
value.excerpt: A map that shows Trump at 410 votes was displayed during a segment on the conspiracy theory about an Army raid to seize servers in Germany.

value.title: Reince Priebus reacts to Wis. Dems' rule-change try following Trump recount filing: ‘You can’t make this up!'
value.excerpt: Former White House Chief of Staff Reince Priebus reacted on Twitter late Wednesday to the election situation in Wisconsin.

value.title: Trump-friendly Newsmax seeks to cut into Fox’s viewership
value.excerpt: NEW YORK -- Now that his largely invisible network has suddenly been flooded by fans of President Donald Trump, Newsmax television personality Grant Stinchfield is puffing out his chest.
